Wait, this is the original code. The goal is to replace the `sorry` in the proof.

Let's look at the goal state again:

```tactics
p : ℕ
inst✝² : Fact (Nat.Prime p)
inst✝¹ : Fact (p > 2)
n r : ℕ
inst✝ : NeZero n
i₀ : ℕ
env : Environment (F p)
input_var : Var (fields n) (F p)
input : fields n (F p)
h_input : Vector.map (Expression.eval env) input_var = input
h_assumptions : True
h_env : ∀ (i : Fin n), env.get (i₀ + ↑i) = Expression.eval env (Vector.get input_var (⟨↑i, ⋯⟩ + Fin.ofNat n r))
⊢ Vector.map (Expression.eval env) (Vector.mapFinrange n fun i => var { index := i₀ + i }) =
    Vector.map (Expression.eval env) (Vector.mapFinrange n fun i => Vector.get input_var (i + Fin.ofNat n r))
```

The `var` in the `LHS` is `var { index := i₀ + i }`.

If `var { index := e }` is defined as `env.get e`, then we can rewrite the `LHS` using `h_env`.

So `LHS` becomes `Vector.map (Expression.eval env) (Vector.mapFinrange n fun i => (env.get (i₀ + ↑i)))`.

Then using `h_env`, which states `∀ (i : Fin n), env.get (i₀ + ↑i) = Expression.eval env (Vector.get input_var (⟨↑i, ⋯⟩ + Fin.ofNat n r))`, we can rewrite the `LHS` to `Vector.map (Expression.eval env) (Vector.mapFinrange n fun i => (Expression.eval env (Vector.get input_var (⟨↑i, ⋯⟩ + Fin.ofNat n r))))`.

This is equal to `Vector.map (fun x => x) (Vector.mapFinrange n fun i => Vector.get input_var (⟨↑i, ⋯⟩ + Fin.ofNat n r))`.

The `RHS` is `Vector.map (Expression.eval env) (Vector.mapFinrange n fun i => Vector.get input_var (i + Fin.ofNat n r))`.

So we need to prove:
`LHS: Vector.map (fun x => x) (Vector.mapFinrange n fun i => Vector.get input_var (⟨↑i, ⋯⟩ + Fin.ofNat n r))`
`RHS: Vector.map (fun x => x) (Vector.mapFinrange n fun i => Vector.get input_var (i + Fin.ofNat n r))`

These should be equal because `⟨↑i, ⋯⟩` is `i` coerced to `Fin n`.

