Wait, the `sorry` placeholders are in the soundness and completeness proofs. We need to replace these.

But looking at the proof goal:

```tactics
⊢ Vector.map (Expression.eval env) (Vector.maprange n fun i => var { index := i₀ + i }) =
    Vector.map (Expression.eval env) (Vector.mapFinrange n fun i => Vector.get input_var (i + Fin.ofNat n r))
```

This is a very low-level equality. To prove this, we can use `funext` to introduce an arbitrary index `i`, and then show that the elements are equal.

```tactics
import Clean.Circuit
import Clean.Utils.Field
import Clean.Utils.Tactics

namespace Circomlib
variable {p : ℕ} [Fact p.Prime] [Fact (p > 2)]

/-
Original source code:
https://github.com/iden3/circomlib/blob/master/circuits/sha256/rotate.circom
-/

namespace RotR

/-
template RotR(n, r) {
    signal input inp[n];
    signal output out[n];

    for (var i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        out[i] <== inp[ (i+r)%n ];
    }
}
-/
def main (n r : ℕ) [NeZero n] (inp : Vector (Expression (F p)) n) := do
  let out <== Vector.mapFinrange n fun i => inp.get (i + Fin.ofNat n r)
  return out

